 that we're hit with a multitude of them.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 3095<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/29/03 10:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=139.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/zilla.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Comets: How Big A Threat To Earth?</span><hr size=1> Can you locate that article for me Hamster. I'll add that to the Gnaw n' Pis article. Those readers scared of nuclear power might also have watched 'Deep Impact'. We may aswell use fear tactics ourselves if that's how the opposition wants to play. Showing up Karl Grossman aswell as Bruce Gagnon would be a bonus.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 784<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/31/03 11:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=139.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/zilla.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Comets: How Big A Threat To Earth?</span><hr size=1> Grossman shows his willingness to bury his head in the sand in his book &quot;The Wrong Stuff.&quot;  Here's what he has to say on page 138 concerning threats from asteroids:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;By that time [when an asteroid hits Earth].&quot; declared Dr. Park, &quot;civilization, if we haven't destroyed it, will presumably be better equipped to deal with the problem.  In defending Earth against this miniscule threat, the Star Warriors would create a vastly greater hazard of nuclear missiles at the ready.&quot;....  Dr. Park repeated that the &quot;frequency [of impacts] is so slight that to start making preparations now makes no sense at all.  What does make sense is to track the asteroids.  Once you have the asteroids tracked we know where they are going to go for the next couple of hundred years&quot; and that would provide adequate time to &quot;mount a defense against an asteroid.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Interesting that he completely leaves out comets.  Comets aren't usually detected hundreds of years in advance before they come relatively close to Earth.  Many of them aren't even discovered until they're in the inner Solar System.  The SOHO satellite is living proof of that and the Shoemakers certainly wouldn't disagree.  But worry not!  We need not take actions now to insure that we aren't hit by the big one.  And also, who says we'd try to blow these things up with nuclear missiles?  There are other nuclear propulsion technologies out there that could be applied to this problem to impart even a slight thrust to the asteroid to change its orbit.  I don't know of anyone who advocates blowing an asteroid into a million pieces as a solution.  Grossman is setting up a strawman and then tearing it down. <br>
